= By popularity =

The kits are ranked in very rough terms of popularity, as measured by the number of stars on their !GitHub repository (updated 27 March 2026).

'Active' indicates that there have been contributions to the repo within the last 12 months.

'Keybindings' indicates whether it ships with standard Emacs bindings or Evil-mode (Vim) modal bindings. If you're starting out and you don't already have the muscle memory for things like hjkl navigation or insert/command modes from using Vim or similar editors, consider using the standard Emacs keybindings because it will be easier for you to find help.

'Description' is taken from the description of the project in Github.

